<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Indexing Data on LIFTI</title><link>https://mikegoatly.github.io/lifti/docs/indexing-mutations/</link><description>Recent content in Indexing Data on LIFTI</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://mikegoatly.github.io/lifti/docs/indexing-mutations/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Batch Mutations</title><link>https://mikegoatly.github.io/lifti/docs/indexing-mutations/batch-mutations/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mikegoatly.github.io/lifti/docs/indexing-mutations/batch-mutations/</guid><description>&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-csharp" data-lang="csharp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;index&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;BeginBatchChange&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;();&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#204a87;font-weight:bold"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;index&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;AddAsync&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0000cf;font-weight:bold"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;&amp;#34;This is some text associated with A: fizz&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#204a87;font-weight:bold"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;index&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;AddAsync&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0000cf;font-weight:bold"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;&amp;#34;Some buzz text for B&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#204a87;font-weight:bold"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;index&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;AddAsync&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0000cf;font-weight:bold"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#4e9a06"&gt;&amp;#34;Text associated with C is both fizz and buzz&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#204a87;font-weight:bold"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;index&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000"&gt;CommitBatchChangeAsync&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold"&gt;();&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only once &lt;code&gt;CommitBatchChangeAsync&lt;/code&gt; has been called will the new data be available in the index for searching. If a search operation was to have been performed between any of the calls to &lt;code&gt;AddAsync&lt;/code&gt; then the previous snapshot would have been used and it would be as if the new documents had not been added yet.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Removing Data</title><link>https://mikegoatly.github.io/lifti/docs/indexing-mutations/removing-data/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mikegoatly.github.io/lifti/docs/indexing-mutations/removing-data/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="removeasynctkey-key"&gt;RemoveAsync(TKey key)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Removes all indexed data for the given item key.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Removal is considered an index mutation in the same way that adding is, and batches of changes can be sped up by using the &lt;code&gt;BeginBatchChange&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;CommitBatchChangeAsync&lt;/code&gt; methods.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>